Happy Monday❤️

I had a session at @lcflondon_ about my entrepreneurship journey and story. 

My career has been one filled with learning, unlearning, gaining valuable experiences, and building meaningful connections.
 
Starting my career at an early age and being naive about what the future held for me in a less acceptable Creative and professional industry, I learnt to consistently be courageous, move in spite of fear and believe in my gift & the vision God gave me. 
 
Being present at each stage of this journey, continues to give me the power to overcome obstacles and the knowledge to protect my heart and mind along the journey.
 
My advise for any young creative is to Always remember your identity is not tied to your career or profession but to who you are, so work on yourself and on your craft constantly so you can offer your best self to the roles you’re called to.

VICE PRESIDENT OF THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA - V.P. KAMALA HARRIS VISITS GHANA. 🇬🇭 

“When we lift up the economic status of a woman, let’s be clear, we lift up the economic status of her children, her family, her community.  The entire economy benefits.” - V.P. KAMALA HARRIS. 

 An Absolute Honor & A Pleasure 🙏🏾❤️

#Africa #Ghana #Women #entrepreneurship #Leadership #Partnerships #BeautyBusiness #BeautyEcosystem #ValerieLawson ❤️

14 years ago I made a decision to be a full time make up artist. My desire to amplify the beauty in others has been a rewarding journey which came with it’s fair share of challenges evident in the African beauty industry and eco-system.

For this reason, in 2021 I founded @ValerieCaresfoundation to teach, train and empower young women under 35 looking for opportunities in the beauty industry. 

I am Proud to announce I have partnered with @mastercardfoundation to roll out a series of exciting new projects and female led-employability initiatives to help tackle the challenges emerging make up artists face.

My team and I are excited to share more details to empower our community. I present to you the @valeriecaresfoundation.

#ValerieLawson #ValerieCaresFoundation #MasterCardFoundation #Impactthroughbeauty.

Application for the @valeriecaresfoundation 2023 FILL ME WITH COLOR - UPSKILLING PROGRAM is now open!

2023 FILL ME WITH COLOR - UPSKILLING PROJECT is aimed at providing professional makeup artistry and business training to up to 60 participants for a 9 month period starting in May. 

Applications close on the 24th of April,2023. 

Apply through the website 
www.valeriecaresfoundation.org or through my linktree (In Bio)

Please share and tag an artist who will benefit from this program. ❤️❤️❤️

#valeriecaresfoundation #valerielawson #impactthroughbeauty #beautyindustry #MastercardFoundation #Knowledgeshare #upskill
